commitResults.messageTitle: Renamed Duke to Pixel. Added greeting and exit message.
Added echo functionatlity.
Enabled adding tasks and displaying tasks in list.
Enabled marking and unmarking of tasks.
Added support for tracking 3 types of tasks (ToDo, Deadline, Event)
Added automated text UI testing, touched up text formatting.
Added handling of input errors.
Enabled deleting of tasks from list.
Enable automatically saving task list contents
commitResults.messageBody:
Contents of task list are lost after program terminates

It would be better to have records of the task list history after termination

Let's write the contents of the task list to a file
(path: "./data/Pixel.txt") after every update to the task list

That way, the task list contents will be saved and can be retrieved after program termination

commitResults.messageTitle: Merge branch 'branch-Level-7'
Event / Deadline classes: Add support for understanding dates and times
commitResults.messageBody:
Dates and times are treated and recorded as strings

This prevents us from working with dates and times in a meaningful way,
such as calculating remaining time or duration of event

Let's add parsing of input date/time into a LocalDateTime object
Input must now follow the format "YYYY-MM-DD HH:mm"
HH:mm is optional, and defaults to 00:00 if not provided
DateTime is printed in the format "MMM d yyyy HH:mm"

commitResults.messageTitle: Add assertions to verify correctness of TaskList methods
Improve code readability
commitResults.messageBody:
Some of the condition checks are overly complicated and
some methods in Parser class are too long

This unnecessary complexity makes the code harder to read

Let's refactor the code by abstracting out some of the condition checks
and change how the long methods are implemented to avoid duplicating code

This will make the code more readable for future maintainers

commitResults.messageTitle: Sync with master branch
Enable operations on multiple tasks at once
commitResults.messageBody:
Tasks can only be marked, unmarked, or deleted one at a time

This is inefficient if the user wants to perform the same operation on multiple tasks

Let's allow the user to mark or unmark multiple consecutive tasks,
and delete all completed tasks, with a single command

This will make user operations more efficient

New commands:
- markAll <from> <to> - Mark all tasks from <from> to <to> inclusive as done
- unmarkAll <from> <to> - Unmark all tasks from <from> to <to> inclusive as not done
- clear - Delete all completed tasks
